The paper deals with the topic of adversarial attacks on a convolutional neural network (CNN) architecture used for malware detection. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the weaknesses in the architecture, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of CNNs for image classification, which could relate to computer vision (cs.CV).
